Yeh yeh I completely agree, there's definitely something very different about him that separates him from other people with depression.

Even though most of the depression signs and causes are there (he is highly insecure, also extremely emo which actually does have a correlation with depression, and most gay/transgender teenagers do tend to struggle with depression), not everything fits... Being so open about it is extremely contradictory to depression. Most if not all confessions have to be persuaded out of the person by someone else, and even then it is never public.

I hate to be the person that says this, but it's much more likely that he is not depressed but instead just having natural teenage feelings.

Teenagers emotions are extremely exaggerated, that's why they always think they're in love or that breakups end their lives or that their shitty situation is worth crying over at 2 am even though it really sort of isn't. Not saying that their are a fair amount of teenagers who in fact are depressed, but you can usually tell the difference if you take an example of each and compare them. I'm also not saying that transgender issues arent serious or can't cause depression since I can gladly say I've no idea what is like, but his situation lines up so much better with "angsty teenager" than "clinically depressed mess"
